# Model configuration for the Credit Card Optimiser agent.
# Change MODEL_PROVIDER and MODEL_NAME here to switch models globally.
# No code changes needed — just update this file and restart run.sh.

# Local Gemma model via Ollama (fully offline / secure).
# Requires Ollama running: https://ollama.com
# Your transaction reasoning never leaves the machine. Only the live web-search
# step (merchant + card names, no amounts) reaches the internet.
#
# This project targets Google's Gemma family. The optimiser REQUIRES tool
# calling, which the Gemma 4 generation supports on Ollama (earlier Gemma
# generations do not, so they will not work). Pick any Gemma 4 tag:
#   gemma4:e2b   (~7.2GB) — efficient, good for 16GB RAM machines (default)
#   gemma4:e4b   (~9.6GB) — higher quality, needs 16GB+ RAM
#   gemma4       (       ) — alias for the current Gemma 4 default tag
#   gemma4:27b   (~17GB)  — best quality, needs a large-VRAM GPU
MODEL_PROVIDER=ollama
MODEL_NAME=gemma4:e2b
OLLAMA_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434

# --- Optional cloud path: Gemini (NOT offline) ---
# Comment out the Ollama block above and uncomment these to run the same agent on
# Gemini. In this mode the live offer/devaluation check uses Google Search
# grounding instead of the local DuckDuckGo tool. Set credentials in .env
# (copy .env.example): GOOGLE_API_KEY=... , or Vertex AI via
# GOOGLE_GENAI_USE_VERTEXAI=TRUE + GCP project. Note: transaction data then
# leaves your machine, so this trades away the offline/privacy guarantee.
# MODEL_PROVIDER=gemini
# MODEL_NAME=gemini-2.5-flash
